    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The MACRS (Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System) depreciation formula for a 7-year property class is: \n\nMACRS Depreciation = (Cost of Equipment - Residual Value) / (2^(Year - 1) - 1)\n\nHowever, for the first year, the formula is a bit different: \n\nMACRS Depreciation (Year 1) = (Cost of Equipment - Residual Value) / 2\n\nThe rate for the first year is 200% of the depreciation. \n\nTo illustrate, let's say the cost of the equipment is $100,000 and the residual value is $20,000. \n\nMACRS Depreciation (Year 1) = ($100,000 - $20,000) / 2 = $40,000\n\nSo, for the first year, you'd depreciate the equipment by $40,000, or 40% of its cost. \n\nKeep in mind that this is a simplified example, and actual MACRS calculations may be more complex. It's always a good idea to consult with a tax professional or accountant to ensure accurate calculations.",
